                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/1100: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-05T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Maumus from McIlhenny.</p>
                <p>It is suggested that to meet in part budgetary payments for May, you use, with
                    the approval of the Haitian Government, the amount set aside to repay United
                    States Government for food advances. The amount so used to be repaid later from
                    proceeds of loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
